---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Icon from '../../../components/Icon.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="For Municipalities & Media - Ferienwohnungsverein Jungfrau"
  description="Factsheet, contacts, and background for municipal councillors and journalists on the short-term rental debate in the Bernese Oberland."
  langAlt="/fuer-gemeinden-medien/"
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="section page-hero hero--intro">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>For Municipalities &amp; Media</h1>
      <p>Protect housing, sustain tourism, and shape rules that genuinely work on the ground: that's what we bring to the debate – facts, hands-on experience, and a willingness to talk.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Framing -->
  <section class="section section--white">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="intro-grid">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Our Stance</p>
          <h2>A good rule has to do more than send a strong signal.</h2>
          <p>The housing question in the Bödeli is real. Anyone who lives, works, or starts a family here should be able to find affordable housing. At the same time, holiday apartments are part of the local tourism structure: they bring guests to restaurants, shops, mountain railways, and leisure offerings, and they secure income for many private owners.</p>
          <p>That's why, in our view, this is not an either-or. What matters is whether a rule actually protects housing, is legally sound, can be enforced, and respects regional differences. That's exactly where we want to contribute constructively.</p>
        </div>
        <aside class="summary-panel" aria-label="In short">
          <p class="summary-panel__label">In short</p>
          <p>We support effective rules against housing pressure. But we reject rigid bans when milder, verifiable, and already proven solutions achieve the same purpose better.</p>
          <a href="/en/our-proposal/" class="text-link">Our proposal in detail</a>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Arguments -->
  <section class="section section--subtle">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <p class="eyebrow">Factsheet</p>
        <h2>Five Points for a Level-Headed Debate</h2>
        <p>The votes and examples of recent months show one thing above all: the question is not whether municipalities may act. The question is which instrument delivers the most impact on the ground.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="argument-grid">
        <article class="argument-card">
          <Icon name="dot-circle" size={28} />
          <h3>The starting situation isn't the same everywhere.</h3>
          <p>The five Bödeli municipalities – Interlaken, Unterseen, Matten, Wilderswil, and Bönigen – are discussing five different approaches. That argues against a blanket "ban wave" and in favour of models that take municipal size, housing structure, tourism intensity, and enforceability seriously.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="argument-card">
          <Icon name="check-square" size={28} />
          <h3>Wilderswil shows a pragmatic path.</h3>
          <p>The Wilderswil model combines a 70% primary-residence quota with a 5-night minimum stay. It was adopted with 83.5% approval; the SP subsequently withdrew its own initiative. That's a strong signal for a broadly accepted, proportionate solution.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="argument-card">
          <Icon name="exclamation-triangle" size={28} />
          <h3>Bans are no guarantee against housing shortages.</h3>
          <p>International examples urge caution. New York's far-reaching Airbnb ban neither lowered rents nor increased vacancy. Protecting housing takes more than a simple cap on paper.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="argument-card">
          <Icon name="cogs" size={28} />
          <h3>Enforcement decides the impact.</h3>
          <p>Even a clear rule achieves little if it can't be implemented. In the city of Bern, the rule adopted with 81% approval is still not in force; in Geneva, an analysis found nearly half of hosts violate the existing 90-day rule.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="argument-card argument-card--wide">
          <Icon name="puzzle-piece" size={28} />
          <h3>Common foundations help everyone.</h3>
          <p>SECO and SEM are preparing a nationwide, unified registration scheme (as of January 2025). We support this development, because better data and uniform procedures help municipalities more than a patchwork of barely comparable individual rules.</p>
        </article>
      </div>

      <p class="source-note">All figures and sources in detail: <a href="/en/sources/">Sources</a> and <a href="/en/our-proposal/">Our Proposal</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- An open conversation -->
  <section class="section section--white">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="offer-band">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">An Open Conversation</p>
          <h2>We don't want to block – we want to help shape.</h2>
          <p>Municipalities are under pressure to deliver quick, visible answers. We bring the perspective of rental practice: which rules are enforceable? Where do unintended side effects arise? And how can housing be protected without needlessly weakening tourism structures that work?</p>
          <p>We're glad to take part in workshops, hearings, or background conversations and help develop a model that fits each municipality.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="offer-actions">
          <p class="offer-contact">Your media contact:<br /><strong>Franz Hefti</strong> · Media &amp; Communications</p>
          <a href="/en/contact/" class="btn btn-accent">Get in touch</a>
          <a href="/en/sources/" class="text-link">View sources</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .intro-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.6fr) minmax(280px, 0.8fr);
    gap: var(--space-6);
    align-items: start;
  }

  .eyebrow {
    margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .summary-panel,
  .offer-band,
  .argument-card {
    border: 1px solid rgba(0, 77, 122, 0.14);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    background: var(--color-white);
  }

  .summary-panel {
    padding: var(--space-4);
    border-top: 4px solid var(--color-accent);
    box-shadow: 0 16px 36px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.08);
  }

  .summary-panel p {
    max-width: none;
  }

  .summary-panel__label {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-1);
    color: var(--color-primary);
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .text-link {
    display: inline-flex;
    width: fit-content;
    margin-top: var(--space-2);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .section-heading {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    max-width: 760px;
  }

  .section-heading p:last-child {
    max-width: 70ch;
  }

  .argument-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-3);
  }

  .argument-card {
    padding: var(--space-3);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-card);
  }

  .argument-card svg {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .argument-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
  }

  .argument-card p {
    max-width: none;
  }

  .argument-card--wide {
    grid-column: 1 / -1;
  }

  .argument-card--wide p {
    max-width: 82ch;
  }

  .source-note {
    margin-top: var(--space-4);
  }

  .offer-band {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) auto;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    align-items: center;
    padding: var(--space-4);
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-white) 0%, var(--color-bg-subtle) 100%);
  }

  .offer-actions {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: var(--space-2);
  }

  .offer-contact {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-1);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .intro-grid,
    .argument-grid,
    .offer-band {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .offer-actions {
      width: 100%;
    }
  }
</style>
